Returns the remaining items of this iterator as a slice.

# Examples

```
let mut vec = vec!['a', 'b', 'c'];
let mut drain = vec.drain(..);
assert_eq!(drain.as_slice(), &['a', 'b', 'c']);
let _ = drain.next().unwrap();
assert_eq!(drain.as_slice(), &['b', 'c']);
```
